Chaos during his first radiation therapy session in Pretoria. JOHANNESBURG - Chaos, the lion from the Lory Park Zoo, underwent his second round of radiation for skin cancer at the Mediclinic Muelmed in Pretoria on Wednesday. The lion is being treated for skin cancer on his nose, after being diagnosed with the rare condition in April. READ: Lion still on the loose, community concerned Now recovering after his second session, the 16-year-old big cat will undergo further treatment in the next few weeks. According to his vet, Chaos is responding very well to the treatment. Chaos, the lion, during his first radiation therapy session last week Tuesday. Chaos during his second radiation treatment session. Chaos, the lion during his second radiation treatment session on 15 May, 2019.